A vintage-style illustration of hands arranging rough paper sketches and wireframe drawings on a wooden drafting table, with scissors, pencils, and sticky notes scattered around. The sketches show simple hand-drawn rectangles representing interface layouts, some cut out and rearranged. Warm sepia tones with soft cream paper textures, reminiscent of 1950s instructional manuals. Morning sunlight streams through a nearby window casting gentle shadows across the workspace. The scene emphasizes tactile, low-tech prototyping with an artisanal, craftsmanship quality—paper fragments with rough torn edges, eraser shavings, and coffee ring stains on the wood surface.
